# Template JSON — do not edit by default

Unless the user **explicitly** asks to change template or section-group JSON:

- **Do not** modify files under `templates/*.json` (e.g. `index.json`, `page.json`, `product.json`).
- **Do not** modify `sections/*-group.json` (e.g. `footer-group.json`, `header-group.json`).

These files control default page layout and Theme Editor presets on deploy. Changing them can overwrite merchant customizations when pushed.

**Instead:** change `sections/*.liquid`, `snippets/`, `assets/`, and `config/settings_schema.json` as needed. Tell the user to adjust section order, blocks, and homepage content in the Theme Editor if layout/preset updates are required.

**Exception:** Only edit template/group JSON when the user clearly requests it (e.g. "update index.json", "add hero to homepage JSON").
